#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn34.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn34.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 34 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 34 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Jhānavagga → samādhisaṃyuttaṃ (bj) | jhāna (or samādhi) saṃyuttaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn34.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Jhānavagga "
msgstr "1. Absorption "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Samādhimūlakasamāpattisutta → samāpattikusalasuttaṃ (bj) | samādhi-samāpatti (pts1)
msgctxt "sn34.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Samādhimūlakasamāpattisutta "
msgstr "1. Entering Immersion "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.264, sc1
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four meditators. "

msgctxt "sn34.1:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo. "
msgstr "One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in entering it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.5"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo. "
msgstr "One meditator is not skilled in immersion but is skilled in entering it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.6"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo. "
msgstr "One meditator is skilled neither in immersion nor in entering it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.7"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca. "
msgstr "One meditator is skilled both in immersion and in entering it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.8"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca. "
msgstr "Of these, the meditator skilled in immersion and in entering it is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the four. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo tatra aggamakkhāyati; "
msgstr "From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.10"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the meditator skilled in immersion and entering it is the foremost, best, leading, highest, and finest of the four.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn34.1:1.11"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

